Ask HN: What backup strategy for laptop with small internal storage?
text:
Hi Community,

I work on a MacBook Pro with a 250 GB internal drive. Suppose that all my files make up 500 GB, 200 GB of which I need on my laptop at any time and 300 GB I am happy to archive on an external hard drive.

What is the best backup strategy assuming that I don't want any of the data to be pushed to the Cloud?

Currently, I have a large enough external hard drive that stores my Time Machine Backups plus a separate directory that contains the 300 GB.

In case my laptop fails, I have my Time Machine backup. In case my external hard drive fails, my 300 GB archive is gone.

Is the best solution to get a second hard drive to mirror the first? If so, what software allows me to easily do that?

I suppose this is a common situation for Mac users due to the expensive storage and I would appreciate to hear about your approaches. Thanks!

Show HN: AI Swiss Army knife for devs in IDE to debug, test code, ask questions
text:
As we have been working on helping developers collaborate and accelerate their productivity, we started to look at ways to enlist AI in this cause. We started working with various AI models.

That led us to launching Bito AI today on Product Hunt. If you have a Product Hunt account, we’d love your support: https://www.producthunt.com/posts/use-bito-ai-to-be-a-10x-de...

Bito AI, https://bito.co, is like a Swiss Army knife for developers, enabling them to use AI to 10x their productivity. Our tool lives in the developer’s IDE and in Chrome and makes it easy via an intuitive chat interface to write code, understand syntax, write test cases, explain code, comment code, check security, and even explain high level concepts.

Trained on billions of lines of code and millions of documents, leveraging OpenAI, we think it’s pretty incredible what we can help devs do without having to search the web or waste time on tedious stuff.

Check out our 2-minute video: https://bit.ly/BitoDemo . If you want to enjoy a laugh at our expense, check out our Bear-Human GPT-6 Dall-e 2 demo: https://bit.ly/3Ya9NWy

Love to get your feedback!
